SIMPLE: update
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: update
<hw>up"date</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧p"d⟦amac⟧t` or ⟦ucr⟧p*d⟦amac⟧t")</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make corrections or to add new
information to (a document) so as to include the most recent
information; <as>as, we <ex>update</ex> the sales database every
night</as>; the book was <ex>updated</ex> and sold as a new edition.
Used often of computerized data bases and documents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>


<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inform (a person) of the most recent information
concerning a topic; <as>as, I <ex>updated</ex> the director on the
status of the project</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>update</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: update
<hw>up"date</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧p"d⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The event or process of updating (in either sense); the information
provided in the process of updating; <as>as, I gave the director the
latest <ex>update</ex> on the project; the <ex>update</ex> took over an
hour</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The document or database which results from a
process of updating; and updated document or database; <as>as, they
distributed the <ex>update</ex> over the internet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Updive</ent>⟦br⟧
